<subSubSection id="C29C653B297AFF80FF07FB7CFC616560" pageId="8" pageNumber="131" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8A3936B0297AFF80FF07FB7CFEC364D5" blockId="8.[189,292,1166,1192]" box="[189,292,1166,1192]" pageId="8" pageNumber="131">
<heading id="D17181DC297AFF80FF07FB7CFEC364D5" bold="true" box="[189,292,1166,1192]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="131" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA2297AFF80FF07FB7CFEC364D5" bold="true" box="[189,292,1166,1192]" pageId="8" pageNumber="131">Remark</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A3936B0297AFF80FF07FB4EFC616560" blockId="8.[189,1398,1212,1310]" pageId="8" pageNumber="131">
Intraspecific variation of the colour of the disc of the hind wings exists in this species, with specimens showing either bright yellow hind wings (
<figureCitation id="12BD2A35297AFF80FD16FB2DFD136487" box="[684,756,1247,1274]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[240,1342,269,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-11@9.[230,1357,265,1889]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Pyrops condorinus (Lallemand, 1960), holotype ♂ (FSAG). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Habitus, lateral view. D. Head and thorax, lateral view. E. Labels and genitalia tube. F. Head, perpendicular view of frons. G. Apex of cephalic process, anteroventral view. D–G = not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468108/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="131">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) or milky white hind wings (
<figureCitation id="12BD2A35297AFF80FBF7FB2DFB716487" box="[1101,1174,1247,1274]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,233,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[254,1335,271,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[243,1345,265,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. Pyrops condorinus (Lallemand, 1960), ♂, Vietnam, Phu Quoc N.P., 14 Apr. 2013 (VNMN). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Habitus, lateral view. D. Head and thorax, lateral view. E. Head, perpendicular view of frons. F. Apex of cephalic process, anteroventral view. D–F = not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468110/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="131">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Conspecificity of both forms was confirmed by the study of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
